Second Lady Karen Pence held a meeting with military service secretaries to discuss military spouse employment challenges and the military's response to the COVID-19 pandemic. The Department of Homeland Security also participated in the meeting. The discussion focused on how each branch will support military spouses and their families as America reopens. Mrs. Pence provided an overview of her military spouse initiative and the current concerns regarding employment and mental health. The service secretaries then provided updates on their efforts to support military spouses, with a focus on occupational licensing, teleworking accommodations, and career training services. The meeting also allowed for questions and further discussion on best practices and collaboration among the branches. Specific policies addressed included military family support, job flexibility during relocation, licensing reform, employment resources, and entrepreneurial opportunities. Vice President Mike Pence also made a surprise appearance to thank the participants for their work in supporting military families.